ce:section.ce:para:
It was essential to perform initial experiments to verify the practicability of an experimental design before incorporating it. The most significant independent factors were selected after considering the effects of various experimental conditions on the fluorescence quenching of N-CQDs by adipoRon. In the initial trials, many experimental variables were examined, including the effects of buffer pH, buffer volume, and incubation time. After testing the impact of different experimental conditions on the fluorescence quenching of N-CQDs by adipoRon, the most influential independent variables were revealed to be buffer pH and buffer volume, while incubation time had little impact on the response. Two experiments were performed, one at the highest levels and one at the lowest levels, to identify the domain for each factor. The chosen range for the buffer's pH was (4–6), and that for the buffer's volume was (1–2 mL). Four planned experiments were used for 22 FFD to find the settings that produce the optimum response values (Table 1
                           ). The obtained response (RFI) from every experiment was noted and entered into the Minitab software. Maximizing values for both individual (d) and composite (D) desirability was done using the response optimizer. Then, using the optimization plot, the most advantageous experimental conditions that yield the best response were identified (Fig. 2
                           ). The study was then carried out under the chosen ideal conditions.
